    # fill dp table using recurrence relation
    for i in range(1, N+1):
        for j in range(M+1):
            # try to climb to step i without breaking any steps
            dp[i][j] = (dp[i-1][j] + dp[i-2][j]) % (10**9+7)
            # try to climb to step i, breaking at least j steps
            dp[i][j+1] = (dp[i-1][j+1] + dp[i-2][j+1]) % (10**9+7)
            # exclude the case where we break the step i itself
            if i-1 not in a[:j+1]:

    # answer is the number of ways to reach step N, with M broken steps
    return str(dp[N][M])
